{"ayat_mp3":"https://everyayah.com/data/Alafasy_128kbps/002229.mp3","arabic":"ٱلطَّلَٰقُ مَرَّتَانِۖ فَإِمۡسَاكُۢ بِمَعۡرُوفٍ أَوۡ تَسۡرِيحُۢ بِإِحۡسَٰنٖۗ وَلَا يَحِلُّ لَكُمۡ أَن تَأۡخُذُواْ مِمَّآ ءَاتَيۡتُمُوهُنَّ شَيۡـًٔا إِلَّآ أَن يَخَافَآ أَلَّا يُقِيمَا حُدُودَ ٱللَّهِۖ فَإِنۡ خِفۡتُمۡ أَلَّا يُقِيمَا حُدُودَ ٱللَّهِ فَلَا جُنَاحَ عَلَيۡهِمَا فِيمَا ٱفۡتَدَتۡ بِهِۦۗ تِلۡكَ حُدُودُ ٱللَّهِ فَلَا تَعۡتَدُوهَاۚ وَمَن يَتَعَدَّ حُدُودَ ٱللَّهِ فَأُوْلَٰٓئِكَ هُمُ ٱلظَّٰلِمُونَ","bengali":"তালাকে-‘রাজঈ’ হ’ল দুবার পর্যন্ত তারপর হয় নিয়মানুযায়ী রাখবে, না হয় সহৃদয়তার সঙ্গে বর্জন করবে। আর নিজের দেয়া সম্পদ থেকে কিছু ফিরিয়ে নেয়া তোমাদের জন্য জায়েয নয় তাদের কাছ থেকে। কিন্তু যে ক্ষেত্রে স্বামী ও স্ত্রী উভয়েই এ ব্যাপারে ভয় করে যে, তারা আল্লাহর নির্দেশ বজায় রাখতে পারবে না, অতঃপর যদি তোমাদের ভয় হয় যে, তারা উভয়েই আল্লাহর নির্দেশ বজায় রাখতে পারবে না, তাহলে সেক্ষেত্রে স্ত্রী যদি বিনিময় দিয়ে অব্যাহতি নিয়ে নেয়, তবে উভয়ের মধ্যে কারোরই কোন পাপ নেই। এই হলো আল্লাহ কর্তৃক নির্ধারিত সীমা। কাজেই একে অতিক্রম করো না। বস্তুতঃ যারা আল্লাহ কর্তৃক নির্ধারিত সীমা লঙ্ঘন করবে, তারাই জালেম।","english":"The divorce is twice, after that, either you retain her on reasonable terms or release her with kindness. And it is not lawful for you (men) to take back (from your wives) any of your Mahr (bridal money given by the husband to his wife at the time of marriage) which you have given them, except when both parties fear that they would be unable to keep the limits ordained by Allah (e.g. to deal with each other on a fair basis). Then if you fear that they would not be able to keep the limits ordained by Allah, then there is no sin on either of them if she gives back (the Mahr or a part of it) for her Al-Khul' (divorce). These are the limits ordained by Allah, so do not transgress them. And whoever transgresses the limits ordained by Allah, then such are the Zalimun (wrong-doers, etc)","wbw":[{"bengali":"তালাক","english":"The divorce","en_t":"al-talaqu","arabic":"ٱلطَّلَٰقُ","ar_mp3":"https://words.audios.quranwbw.com/2/002_229_001.mp3"},{"bengali":"দুইবার","english":"(is) twice","en_t":"marratani","arabic":"مَرَّتَانِۖ","ar_mp3":"https://words.audios.quranwbw.com/2/002_229_002.mp3"},{"bengali":"অতঃপর রেখে দেওয়া ","english":"Then to retain","en_t":"fa-im'sakun","arabic":"فَإِمۡسَاكُۢ","ar_mp3":"https://words.audios.quranwbw.com/2/002_229_003.mp3"},{"bengali":"ন্যায়সংগত ভাবে","english":"in a reasonable manner","en_t":"bima'rufin","arabic":"بِمَعۡرُوفٍ","ar_mp3":"https://words.audios.quranwbw.com/2/002_229_004.mp3"},{"bengali":"অথবা","english":"or","en_t":"aw","arabic":"أَوۡ","ar_mp3":"https://words.audios.quranwbw.com/2/002_229_005.mp3"},{"bengali":"মুক্ত করে দেয়া","english":"to release (her)","en_t":"tasrihun","arabic":"تَسۡرِيحُۢ","ar_mp3":"https://words.audios.quranwbw.com/2/002_229_006.mp3"},{"bengali":"সদয়ভাবে (উত্তম)","english":"with kindness","en_t":"bi-ih'sanin","arabic":"بِإِحۡسَٰنٖۗ","ar_mp3":"https://words.audios.quranwbw.com/2/002_229_007.mp3"},{"bengali":"এবং না","english":"And (it is) not","en_t":"wala","arabic":"وَلَا","ar_mp3":"https://words.audios.quranwbw.com/2/002_229_008.mp3"},{"bengali":"বৈধ হবে","english":"lawful","en_t":"yahillu","arabic":"يَحِلُّ","ar_mp3":"https://words.audios.quranwbw.com/2/002_229_009.mp3"},{"bengali":"তোমাদের জন্যে","english":"for you","en_t":"lakum","arabic":"لَكُمۡ","ar_mp3":"https://words.audios.quranwbw.com/2/002_229_010.mp3"},{"bengali":"যে","english":"that","en_t":"an","arabic":"أَن","ar_mp3":"https://words.audios.quranwbw.com/2/002_229_011.mp3"},{"bengali":"তোমরা গ্রহণ করবে","english":"you take (back)","en_t":"takhudhu","arabic":"تَأۡخُذُواْ","ar_mp3":"https://words.audios.quranwbw.com/2/002_229_012.mp3"},{"bengali":"তা থেকে যা","english":"whatever","en_t":"mimma","arabic":"مِمَّآ","ar_mp3":"https://words.audios.quranwbw.com/2/002_229_013.mp3"},{"bengali":"তোমরা দিয়েছ তাদেরকে","english":"you have given them","en_t":"ataytumuhunna","arabic":"ءَاتَيۡتُمُوهُنَّ","ar_mp3":"https://words.audios.quranwbw.com/